<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 3: MANIFOLDS - VALVE COVER/INTAKE
        MANIFOLD - INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If valve cover/intake manifold gasket is not damaged and in good condition, it can be reused.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place gasket onto cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hold the valve cover/intake manifold over the engine. Place a new O-ring into the wiring
                harness connector port and push the connector in until the tabs lock.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                        THE VALVE COVER/INTAKE MANIFOLD AND GASKET ALIGN PROPERLY.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the valve cover/intake manifold onto the cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure valve cover/intake manifold to the cylinder head using thirteen (13) mounting
                capscrews (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600312">3.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ). Tighten to the special torque value.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600312" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg6845" filename="../figeg6/EG6845.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.12 Valve Cover/Intake Manifold Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate and install a new O-Ring onto the road draft tube (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e160_70.xml" xrefid="ef1600313">3.13</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the draft tube into the bore located on the rear right hand side of the valve
                cover/intake manifold. Secure the road draft tube to the crankcase using two (2) mounting bolts and
                tighten (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e160_70.xml" xrefid="ef1600314">3.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
